	   <tr><td colspan=2>New mages = dont even WORRY about the epic pet.  We all know that it is the most powerful thing in the game, blah blah blah...but you are not going to get this pet overnight.  Dont even bother playing a mage for the epic pet.  You can dream about it all you want, but you are not going to get it ever, if you are not good at playing a mage or if you dont truly enjoy playing a mage.  Obviously this pet is mega good and all, but dont think of it as the main focus of playing a mage.  Instead think of the epic as a side reward for raising a magician's power and level.  The real power in a magician is not this pet, like so many of you newbies believe, but the playing skill and abilities of the mage himself.<br><br>I don't ever want to see a mage out there playing just for the epic.  First of all, if you dont enjoy your class, you'll probably get bored and quit.  Second, if you are tagging along just for the epic, well, i dont want to see that either, because usually those mages are not good players.  So if you are getting all excited about this epic pet, you should first play to level 16 or 20 or so, to see if you truly enjoy the class.  My point is basically DO NOT BOTHER WITH THE MAGE CLASS IF YOU DONT LIKE IT, DONT USE THIS AS YOUR ONLY MOTIVATION TO PLAY MAGE.(you probably wont be doing the epic until level 54 or 55 or so, so you have a long way to go)<br><br>Tannaydar 49 magician<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
