<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=98825507390889></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f98825507390889><tr><td id=headerrow><span id=sj><a href=/strategy/classes.html?class=12&mid=98825507390889>RE: Epic pet</a></span></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Wed, Apr 25th 11:17 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>If you are new to the game, don't worry about the epic pet for a long, long time. Even if you were a terrific player with lots of time to devote to EQ, it would take you a few months of hard playing to even get to a level where you can finish up the quest.<br><br>Epic quests (there is one for each class) are designed to be a true test of your skill and patience in playing the game. They take you from one end of Norrath to the other. Some of the monsters you have to kill are extremely rare, and don't always drop the necessary items. Others aren't rare, but they are such high level that it does take the cooperation of a group of groups to take it down...and still may not always drop the required components. (This is why you see people  mentioning that you must be in a large guild to do the quests; you have to have quite a few good players to fight some mobs, and you usually have to repeat the experience several times so everyone gets their components.)<br><br>You can rest assured, though, that having the epic pet is by no means required for you to play a successful magician. Your normal pets will serve you quite nicely throughout your career as a magician. Even if you never get your epic weapon, you can still fight in any zone in the game, making your normal high damage and utility contributions, without any detrimental effects whatsoever (assuming you are appropriately grouped for each zone, that is).<br><br>Again, don't even worry about the epic until you are at least level 50, at which point you can start to piece together some of the easier pieces. It's a powerful weapon and pet, but it's not necessary to effectively play the game, and it's really more of a status symbol at any rate. The process of getting the weapon is a true test of your perserverance and skill as a player.<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
